static int list_empty_careful ( const struct list_head *  head  )  [inline, static]

Test whether a list is empty and not being modified.

Parameters:
head the list to test

Tests whether a list is empty _and_ checks that no other CPU might be in the process of modifying either member (next or prev)

NOTE: using list_empty_careful() without synchronization can only be safe if the only activity that can happen to the list entry is list_del_init(). Eg. it cannot be used if another CPU could re-list_add() it.
